g.text: The resource that is the subject of the relationship, identified by a collection_object_id
The resource that is the object of the relationship.
The relationship of the subject (collection_object_id) to the object (related_coll_object_id)
Comments or notes about the relationship between the two resources
The creator of this relationship record
Identifier for a row in biol_indiv_relations. Should be the surrogate numeric primary key.
cataloged items are a subtype of collection objects.
The catalog number of the cataloged item, including any prefix or suffix. Automatically assembled from cat_num_prefix, cat_num_integer, and cat_num_suffix.
The accession under which this cataloged item was brought into the museum.
The collecting event in which this cataloged item was collected.
The collection code for the collection within which this cataloged item is held. Autopopulated convenience field with value obtained from collection.
The type of the cataloged item, FS=fossil voucher, BI=biological preserved specimen, HO=human observation. Broadly corresponds to dwc:basisOfRecord and the Darwin Core classes.
Foreign key to the collection within which this cataloged item is held. Enforces virtual private database limitiations on collection.
The prefix portion of the catalog number, if any. Including any separator. Example "R-"
The numeric portion of the catalog number.
The suffix portion of the catalog number, if any. Including any separator. Example "-a"
Something to which a catalog number is assigned in a collection.
type of collection object record, for cataloged item or for part thereof. Domain: SP, CI, SS
The agent who created the collection object record.
The date on which the collection object record was created.
The agent who most recently edited the collection object record.
The date on which the collection object record was most recently edited
The current disposition of the collection object.
The number of items making up the collection object.
The current condition of the collection object
A textual modifier for the lot count indicating range or uncertainty in the count.
Remarks concerning the current condition of the collection object.
The cataloged item to which the remarks apply
Comments or notes regarding the disposition of the collection object.
Comments or notes regarding the specimen.
Microhabitat information related to the gathering of the collection object. See also collecting_event.habitat_desc for habitat information.
Species found in association with the collection object in its gathering.
